00:19:57,781 --> 00:20:03,600
You can click in a blank space on the
canvas to make sure it's de-selected.

242
00:20:03,601 --> 00:20:06,360
And in your visualizations pane,

243
00:20:06,360 --> 00:20:10,800
you're gonna find and select
the slicer visualization icon.

244
00:20:10,801 --> 00:20:14,240
It looks like a table with a funnel on it.

245
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:22,000
And it popped the slicer over
on the right side of the screen.

246
00:20:22,001 --> 00:20:25,240
If it didn't place it there,
you can move it over there.

247
00:20:26,139 --> 00:20:31,600
And now what we're gonna do,
in the store table in the fields pane,

248
00:20:31,601 --> 00:20:35,720
we're gonna just drag
chain over to the slicer.

249
00:20:36,819 --> 00:20:40,940
And we realize the slicer
doesn't have to be that tall.

250
00:20:40,989 --> 00:20:43,000
So I'm gonna resize it.

251
00:20:44,799 --> 00:20:47,700
Doesn't need to take up that much space.

252
00:20:49,949 --> 00:20:54,700
And I decide that I'm gonna do a
little bit of formatting to this slicer.

253
00:20:56,099 --> 00:21:03,100
With the slicer selected, I'm going to
the format well in the visualizations pane.

254
00:21:03,101 --> 00:21:07,340
And I'm gonna just enable a
background color for the slicer,

255
00:21:07,589 --> 00:21:12,340
expand background and
choose a complimentary color.

256
00:21:15,200 --> 00:21:19,440
I'm also fond of putting
borders around slicers,

257
00:21:19,441 --> 00:21:23,200
just so they stand out a
little bit more on the page.

258
00:21:23,249 --> 00:21:26,900
So I've collapsed the
background format option,

259
00:21:26,901 --> 00:21:31,680
and I'm gonna enable
border and expand it.

260
00:21:32,529 --> 00:21:35,676
And I'm gonna leave the
border black, but I'm gonna

261
00:21:35,677 --> 00:21:39,500
make it about 30 pixels
in radius so it stands out.

262
00:21:41,999 --> 00:21:47,200
And now when I click away from the
slicer, you'll see the border around it.

263
00:21:49,199 --> 00:21:52,610
Let's test the slicer
on this page before we

264
00:21:52,611 --> 00:21:56,360
sync and make it visible
on the other two pages.

265
00:21:56,360 --> 00:22:02,040
So in the slicer, I'm gonna just
check the box in front of fashions direct,

266
00:22:02,041 --> 00:22:05,880
and it filtered the
visualization for that chain.

267
00:22:05,881 --> 00:22:09,480
I'm gonna uncheck that box
so I get both chains showing.

268
00:22:10,779 --> 00:22:16,360
Now with your slicer still selected, you're
gonna go up to the View tab of the ribbon.

269
00:22:16,361 --> 00:22:20,380
And the last button on the
View tab is Sync Slicers.

270
00:22:21,979 --> 00:22:24,520
You really don't have to sync slicers.

271
00:22:24,521 --> 00:22:27,440
If you want a slicer
just on one report page

272
00:22:27,441 --> 00:22:31,160
and only functional on one
report page, you can do that.

273
00:22:31,161 --> 00:22:36,760
But in our case, we wanna use
the same slicer on multiple pages.

274
00:22:36,761 --> 00:22:41,200
When you click on Sync Slicers,
you get a Sync Slicers pane

275
00:22:41,201 --> 00:22:45,320
in between your Filters and
Visualizations panes on the right side.

276
00:22:46,419 --> 00:22:52,020
It will show you all of the
pages in this particular report file.

277
00:22:53,119 --> 00:22:55,160
And there are two columns.

278
00:22:55,161 --> 00:22:58,120
The column with the circular arrow

279
00:22:58,121 --> 00:23:01,860
that represents whether
the slicer is gonna be synced.

280
00:23:01,909 --> 00:23:05,920
So if it's on this page and
I sync it with another page,

281
00:23:05,921 --> 00:23:10,860
that means that when I filter on this page,
the other page will be filtered as well.

282
00:23:11,720 --> 00:23:12,820
And vice versa.

283
00:23:14,069 --> 00:23:17,734
The other column looks
like an eye, and that's

284
00:23:17,735 --> 00:23:23,000
whether the slicer will be
visible on the other pages.

285
00:23:23,049 --> 00:23:25,880
So notice the slicer is already visible.

286
00:23:25,881 --> 00:23:26,780
It's already checked.

287
00:23:26,781 --> 00:23:29,800
This is the page that we created it on.

288
00:23:29,800 --> 00:23:35,480
And we're also gonna check the
Sync button after T-Y-L-Y invariant.

289
00:23:35,554 --> 00:23:39,960
So it's synced and visible on this page.

290
00:23:39,960 --> 00:23:44,860
We're gonna select both check boxes
for the Reg versus Markdown page.

291
00:23:46,659 --> 00:23:50,760
And we're gonna select
both for the KPI page.

292
00:23:50,761 --> 00:23:54,787
And usually when you
sync it, a new update has

293
00:23:54,788 --> 00:23:58,260
it automatically checking
that it's also visible.

294
00:23:58,261 --> 00:24:03,240
But if that's not happening, you
will have to click both check boxes.

295
00:24:03,289 --> 00:24:04,820
So what does that do?

296
00:24:05,619 --> 00:24:08,720
At this point, we don't need
Sync Slicers pane open.

297
00:24:08,721 --> 00:24:13,860
So to get rid of some of the clutter, I'm
gonna close that pane by using the X.

298
00:24:15,359 --> 00:24:22,080
And on T-Y-L-Y invariants page,
I'm gonna go ahead and use the slicer

299
00:24:22,279 --> 00:24:24,500
to filter for the Lindsay's chain.

300
00:24:26,099 --> 00:24:32,440
When I go to the Reg versus Markdown
page, you'll notice the slicer is visible,

