filtered for Fashions Direct.

305
00:24:54,554 --> 00:25:01,540
If I go back to T-Y-L-Y invariants page,
that is also filtered for Fashions Direct.

306
00:25:02,439 --> 00:25:08,760
So I'm gonna clear the filter by just
unchecking Fashions Direct in the slicer.

307
00:25:08,761 --> 00:25:12,025
And now, if you look at
the other two pages, they're

308
00:25:12,026 --> 00:25:17,020
showing all of the data, not
just by a particular change.

309
00:25:19,619 --> 00:25:24,960
In this next lesson, we're gonna
focus on creating a drill-through page.

310
00:25:24,960 --> 00:25:30,340
With drill-through in Power BI reports,
you can create a page in your report

311
00:25:30,341 --> 00:25:36,100
that focuses on a specific entity,
such as a category store or territory.

312
00:25:36,949 --> 00:25:39,600
When your report readers use drill-through,

313
00:25:39,600 --> 00:25:43,200
they right-click a data
point in other report pages

314
00:25:43,201 --> 00:25:49,340
and drill-through to the focus page to get
details that are filtered to that context.

315
00:25:49,341 --> 00:25:51,740
You'll see this play out in this lesson.

316
00:25:53,539 --> 00:25:58,560
We're gonna put our drill-through
report on a separate page,

317
00:25:58,959 --> 00:26:02,760
so I'm gonna go ahead and click
the plus sign to get a new page,

318
00:26:02,761 --> 00:26:07,380
and I'm gonna double-click page
one and name the page drill-through.

319
00:26:09,529 --> 00:26:15,200
Remember to press enter after you finish
typing in the name so it accepts the name.

320
00:26:17,199 --> 00:26:20,020
For this type of report
that we're gonna build,

321
00:26:20,819 --> 00:26:24,920
we're gonna use the
multi-row card visualization.

322
00:26:24,921 --> 00:26:30,900
In your visualizations pane, locate
the multi-row card icon and click it.

323
00:26:32,959 --> 00:26:37,820
We're gonna use three fields from
the sales table to populate this card.

324
00:26:37,821 --> 00:26:42,169
The first field we're gonna use
is last year's sales, so I'm gonna

325
00:26:42,170 --> 00:26:46,400
just click and hold and drag it
over into the card framework.

326
00:26:47,874 --> 00:26:53,000
I'm gonna grab the value field from
this year's sales and drag it over.

327
00:26:54,999 --> 00:26:59,860
And the last field is we
want total sales VAR percent.

328
00:27:01,660 --> 00:27:06,797
Once I drag that into the card,
I'm gonna widen the card so

329
00:27:06,798 --> 00:27:10,700
it only displays one row, and
I don't need it to be that tall,

330
00:27:10,701 --> 00:27:15,600
so I'm gonna make it less
tall by using the sizing handles.

331
00:27:18,224 --> 00:27:21,840
At the bottom of the visualization pane,

332
00:27:21,840 --> 00:27:25,256
regardless of the type
of visualization that

333
00:27:25,257 --> 00:27:28,840
you select, you have
a drill-through section.

334
00:27:28,840 --> 00:27:35,040
We're gonna use that section now
