We're seeing the numbers.

449
00:37:06,801 --> 00:37:09,720
It's a multi-row card, right?

450
00:37:09,721 --> 00:37:13,920
We don't want to put a title on the card.

451
00:37:13,921 --> 00:37:18,820
Maybe we do wanna give the card
a border for some visual interest.

452
00:37:18,870 --> 00:37:23,820
So I'm gonna toggle border
to on and expand the category,

453
00:37:23,821 --> 00:37:30,000
and I'm gonna give it a
border color like a bluish color.

454
00:37:32,000 --> 00:37:36,200
And I'm gonna make
the border 30 pixel radius,

455
00:37:36,201 --> 00:37:41,760
and when I click away from
the card, I can see the effect.

456
00:37:41,761 --> 00:37:44,960
It's a little bit more visually appealing.

457
00:37:44,961 --> 00:37:48,840
I'm gonna reselect the card
and go back to the format well,

458
00:37:50,140 --> 00:37:53,840
and I decide I'm gonna give
the card a background color.

459
00:37:53,890 --> 00:37:59,120
So I'm gonna toggle background
to on, expand the category,

460
00:38:00,245 --> 00:38:04,140
and I'm gonna choose a lighter color,

461
00:38:05,540 --> 00:38:07,640
and I'm gonna click away from the card.

462
00:38:09,640 --> 00:38:16,280
In terms of the arrow that comes
when you do a drill through page,

463
00:38:16,281 --> 00:38:22,200
you can actually swap that out
for something else of your choice.

464
00:38:22,201 --> 00:38:24,640
It's actually a second component.

465
00:38:24,641 --> 00:38:28,680
It's kinda sorta on its
own outside of the card.

466
00:38:28,730 --> 00:38:33,100
So if you click on the arrow,
you'll notice that it selects just that.

467
00:38:33,101 --> 00:38:35,700
You'll see the sizing handles around that,

468
00:38:36,850 --> 00:38:40,140
and you can press Delete on your keyboard,

469
00:38:40,141 --> 00:38:44,980
and we're gonna use another
back arrow for our back button.

470
00:38:46,130 --> 00:38:50,640
So what we're gonna want to do is
go up to the Insert tab of the ribbon,

471
00:38:51,540 --> 00:38:54,440
and the last group is the Elements group.

472
00:38:54,441 --> 00:39:00,400
You can insert a text box on a
visualization page, a variety of buttons.

473
00:39:00,401 --> 00:39:04,440
If you look at the buttons,
you'll see the back button.

474
00:39:04,690 --> 00:39:08,900
That's the one that came as a default
when we created this drill through page,

475
00:39:11,300 --> 00:39:14,260
and they have other arrow buttons in here.

476
00:39:15,360 --> 00:39:19,840
We can use an image if
it's stored on your computer.

477
00:39:19,841 --> 00:39:22,160
What we're gonna use is shapes.

478
00:39:22,210 --> 00:39:25,620
So under Shapes, they have block arrows,

479
00:39:25,621 --> 00:39:29,520
and we're gonna select
the arrow left block arrow.

480
00:39:31,170 --> 00:39:35,440
Puts it in pretty big, so I'm
gonna make it really tiny.

481
00:39:41,950 --> 00:39:47,000
And I am going to move
it so that it is right above

482
00:39:51,220 --> 00:39:52,860
my multi-row card.

483
00:39:54,610 --> 00:40:00,760
And with the block arrows still selected,
you'll notice you have another pane.

484
00:40:00,761 --> 00:40:06,020
You have a Format Shape pane that shows up
where the Visualizations pane used to be.

485
00:40:07,320 --> 00:40:11,960
And in that pane, you
have an Action option.

486
00:40:12,060 --> 00:40:18,240
We're gonna enable the
Action option and then expand it,

487
00:40:18,241 --> 00:40:23,440
and you'll see that the default action
is that it serves as a back button,

488
00:40:23,640 --> 00:40:26,468
just like the one that
came when we did this

489
00:40:26,469 --> 00:40:29,120
visualization and
made it a drill through.

490
00:40:29,121 --> 00:40:31,480
You have other choices there.

491
00:40:31,481 --> 00:40:33,380
We're gonna leave it on Back.

492
00:40:34,880 --> 00:40:38,300
And now I'm gonna just
click away from the arrow,

493
00:40:39,250 --> 00:40:43,844
hold down my Control key,
and click on it, and it should

494
00:40:43,845 --> 00:40:49,000
take me back to the Sales
by Category report page.

495
00:40:49,001 --> 00:40:50,760
Go ahead and save your file.

496
00:40:54,735 --> 00:41:02,760
Spend a few moments in the format well, and
give your stacked bar chart data labels,

497
00:41:03,410 --> 00:41:08,180
add a background color, and
a shadow effect if you'd like.

498
00:41:10,205 --> 00:41:15,440
We want to apply the same
formatting to both of our slicers,

499
00:41:15,441 --> 00:41:18,920
so there's a time-saving
technique that you can use.

500
00:41:18,921 --> 00:41:24,920
I'm gonna click at the very top of the
chain slicer, hold down my Control key,

501
00:41:24,921 --> 00:41:29,440
and click at the top of the buyer
slicer so both of them are selected.

502
00:41:31,490 --> 00:41:36,560
In the format well, with
both slicers already selected,

503
00:41:36,760 --> 00:41:45,040
I'm gonna expand Selection Controls, and
make sure Select All option is toggled to On.

504
00:41:46,840 --> 00:41:49,440
I'm gonna collapse Selection Controls,

505
00:41:51,090 --> 00:41:55,020
and I'm gonna expand the background,

506
00:41:55,021 --> 00:41:59,980
and choose a background color that's
complementary to the rest of the page.

507
00:42:01,380 --> 00:42:05,800
So see how it impacts
both slicers at the same time.

508
00:42:06,840 --> 00:42:10,600
Because I chose a dark background color,

509
00:42:11,500 --> 00:42:16,500
I'm gonna expand Items,
and change the item color,

510
00:42:17,650 --> 00:42:22,540
the font color for the items, to white,
so they show up a little bit better.

511
00:42:25,990 --> 00:42:31,085
I'm gonna click on a blank area
of the canvas to deselect both

512
00:42:31,086 --> 00:42:35,900
of those slicers, and I just
need to resize my buyer slicer

513
00:42:35,950 --> 00:42:40,900
so it's the same size as the
chain one for consistency.

514
00:42:42,000 --> 00:42:44,760
Go ahead and save your file.

515
00:42:46,760 --> 00:42:51,560
Just like Excel, Power BI has
a conditional formatting feature.

516
00:42:52,560 --> 00:42:57,320
Let's navigate to our
TYLY and Variants page,

517
00:42:58,470 --> 00:43:03,080
and the first thing we're
gonna do is resize the column

518
00:43:03,130 --> 00:43:06,940
chart visualization so
it's not as tall as it is.

519
00:43:06,941 --> 00:43:09,786
We're gonna wanna
put another visualization

520
00:43:09,836 --> 00:43:12,840
underneath it, so we're
just making space for that.

521
00:43:15,240 --> 00:43:19,300
Conditional formatting
in Power BI lends itself

522
00:43:19,301 --> 00:43:24,300
to the table visualization,
or the matrix visualization.

523
00:43:24,550 --> 00:43:28,200
In the visualization pane,
we're gonna make sure

524
00:43:28,201 --> 00:43:31,640
that we don't have anything
selected on our canvas,

525
00:43:31,641 --> 00:43:35,500
and we're gonna select
the table visualization icon.

526
00:43:38,050 --> 00:43:42,320
From the sales table in the fields pane,

527
00:43:42,321 --> 00:43:47,320
we're gonna wanna add
last year's sales to the table,

528
00:43:47,321 --> 00:43:50,340
so I'm gonna just drag it
into the table framework,

529
00:43:51,890 --> 00:43:58,160
and we're also going to wanna add
this year's sales value into the table.

530
00:43:59,210 --> 00:44:05,020
So we just have two columns in the table,
and that's fine for what we're trying to do.

531
00:44:06,570 --> 00:44:10,583
So in order to do conditional
formatting, you have to

532
00:44:10,584 --> 00:44:14,480
access the field that you
want to conditionally format

533
00:44:14,580 --> 00:44:17,480
from the visualizations pane.

534
00:44:17,481 --> 00:44:24,840
So if you notice, we have last year's sales
and this year's sales in the values box.

535
00:44:24,841 --> 00:44:29,080
We wanna conditionally
format this year's sales.

536
00:44:29,130 --> 00:44:33,745
So I'm gonna right-click on
this year's sales, hover over

537
00:44:33,746 --> 00:44:38,280
conditional formatting, and I'm
gonna click on background color.

538
00:44:41,080 --> 00:44:44,880
So the background
color for the specific field

539
00:44:44,881 --> 00:44:50,540
that we right-click on, this year's sale,
dialog box comes up on the screen.

540
00:44:51,790 --> 00:44:56,820
Take a moment and explore
the format by dropdown.

541
00:44:57,140 --> 00:45:02,120
We're gonna leave it on color scale,
but you do have other options there.

542
00:45:02,121 --> 00:45:06,538
And also take a look at
the apply to dropdown that's

543
00:45:06,539 --> 00:45:10,320
defaulting to values only, and
we're gonna leave it like that.

544
00:45:11,395 --> 00:45:16,720
It tells you it's based on this
field, and that's also a dropdown,

545
00:45:16,770 --> 00:45:19,240
so you could search for
other fields from in here

546
00:45:19,241 --> 00:45:22,680
if you happen to right-click
on the wrong field.

547
00:45:25,120 --> 00:45:29,340
We have a minimum and maximum area,

548
00:45:30,240 --> 00:45:33,938
and before we start
filling in any numbers

549
00:45:33,939 --> 00:45:38,280
here, we're gonna check
the diverging checkbox.

550
00:45:38,281 --> 00:45:43,340
So now we have minimum,
center, and maximum areas to fill out.

551
00:45:45,040 --> 00:45:49,334
The scenario we're using
here is we wanna say that we

552
00:45:49,335 --> 00:45:53,760
have a tolerance for what
this year's sales should be.

553
00:45:53,761 --> 00:45:57,480
We're comfortable with
a minimum of 20 million.

554
00:45:58,430 --> 00:46:03,480
We would like to have
a maximum of 25 million,

555
00:46:04,030 --> 00:46:06,360
and we're kinda okay in the center

556
00:46:06,585 --> 00:46:10,960
if the center is $23,500,000.

557
00:46:11,010 --> 00:46:15,600
So we're gonna start putting
those numbers in boxes.

558
00:46:15,601 --> 00:46:21,140
Under minimum, where it says enter a
value, you're gonna put in your 20 million,

559
00:46:25,510 --> 00:46:30,264
for the center enter a
value box, it's gonna be 23.

560
00:46:32,234 --> 00:46:41,100
5 million, and the maximum
is going to be 25 million.

561
00:46:41,600 --> 00:46:52,440
Before we click okay, let's take
a look at this year's sales value.

562
00:46:52,441 --> 00:46:57,440
22,051,952.

563
00:46:58,490 --> 00:47:03,300
So it's not at the minimum,
certainly not at the maximum.

564
00:47:03,301 --> 00:47:06,320
It's a little bit below center.

565
00:47:06,370 --> 00:47:11,320
So when you're diverging,
there is a color scale there.

566
00:47:11,321 --> 00:47:15,071
If we were directly at
center, it would be this

567
00:47:15,072 --> 00:47:18,960
yellowish color, but we're
a little bit less than center.

568
00:47:19,010 --> 00:47:21,240
So go ahead and click okay,

569
00:47:22,120 --> 00:47:24,480
and look at the color that it used

570
00:47:25,630 --> 00:47:28,080
to highlight this year's sales.

571
00:47:29,730 --> 00:47:32,540
Now keep in mind, if our data changes,

572
00:47:32,940 --> 00:47:38,852
if we add more sales for
this year to our data set, that

573
00:47:38,853 --> 00:47:43,620
color on this year's sales will
change accordingly as well.

574
00:47:43,621 --> 00:47:46,160
That's an example of a conditional format.

575
00:47:48,585 --> 00:47:51,480
Another useful efficiency technique

576
00:47:51,481 --> 00:47:56,480
is using the bookmarks
feature in your Power BI reports.

577
00:47:56,780 --> 00:48:00,200
Let's go to the sales by category page.

578
00:48:00,375 --> 00:48:03,634
And the first thing we
have to do is let's go to

579
00:48:03,635 --> 00:48:07,680
where the dropdown
would be in the buyer slicer.

580
00:48:07,681 --> 00:48:11,814
And remember, we changed
the item color, the font

581
00:48:11,864 --> 00:48:15,640
color to white, so we're
not able to see the items.

582
00:48:15,641 --> 00:48:21,880
I neglected to have you change the
background of the items to a darker color.

583
00:48:21,980 --> 00:48:26,040
So I'm gonna click on
the chain slicer to select it,

584
00:48:26,090 --> 00:48:30,000
hold down my control key
and click on the buyer slicer,

585
00:48:30,001 --> 00:48:33,400
and go to the paint roller
to get into the format well.

586
00:48:34,500 --> 00:48:38,961
I'm gonna expand items
and do the dropdown next to

587
00:48:38,962 --> 00:48:42,880
background color, and I'm
gonna choose a dark color.

588
00:48:43,980 --> 00:48:51,300
If I click on the blank area of the
canvas and go to the buyer all dropdown,

589
00:48:51,301 --> 00:48:54,780
I'll be able to see all of the
buyers names clearly now

590
00:48:54,781 --> 00:48:58,240
because it's a contrasting
background color.

591
00:48:58,241 --> 00:49:01,320
We're gonna select Evangeline Bright.

592
00:49:02,670 --> 00:49:07,620
So now our chart is filtered
for just Evangeline Bright.

593
00:49:07,621 --> 00:49:16,400
Let's say that this report page you come to
often and you filter for different buyers.

594
00:49:16,401 --> 00:49:21,400
You can save your filtered
report as a bookmark.

595
00:49:21,950 --> 00:49:26,080
To do that, you're gonna go
up to the view tab on the ribbon

596
00:49:26,081 --> 00:49:31,520
in the show panes group, the last
group, you're gonna click on bookmarks,

597
00:49:31,521 --> 00:49:35,600
and it opens a panel to the
left of your visualization pane.

598
00:49:36,900 --> 00:49:41,820
With the report filtered for
Evangeline Bright, the way it is,

599
00:49:41,821 --> 00:49:46,360
we're gonna click add at the
top of the bookmarks pane,

600
00:49:46,361 --> 00:49:50,040
and it adds a bookmark,
it calls it bookmark one.

601
00:49:50,041 --> 00:49:53,575
To the right of it, we're
gonna go to the more

602
00:49:53,576 --> 00:49:56,960
options ellipsis, and we're
gonna choose rename,

603
00:49:57,910 --> 00:50:00,680
and we'll just call it Evangeline Bright,

604
00:50:01,805 --> 00:50:04,720
the buyer's name, and press enter.

605
00:50:06,045 --> 00:50:08,800
Now go ahead and close your bookmarks pane

606
00:50:08,801 --> 00:50:11,660
by using the X in the
upper right hand corner.

607
00:50:13,680 --> 00:50:19,440
Access the buyer slicer dropdown,
and choose select all at the top.

608
00:50:20,690 --> 00:50:24,880
The next time that you wanna
see it filtered for Evangeline Bright,

609
00:50:24,881 --> 00:50:30,160
you don't actually have to do the filter,
you just need to access the bookmark.

610
00:50:30,161 --> 00:50:33,560
We're gonna go back to
bookmarks on the view tab,

611
00:50:34,460 --> 00:50:39,020
and in the bookmarks pane, you're
gonna click on Evangeline Bright,

612
00:50:39,920 --> 00:50:42,560
and it does the same filter for you.

613
00:50:42,610 --> 00:50:48,040
So imagine if you set up a bookmark for
those buyers that you wanna track frequently,

614
00:50:48,041 --> 00:50:53,640
you can have multiple bookmarks set
up and access them anytime you need to.

615
00:50:53,641 --> 00:50:56,180
Go ahead and save your file.

616
00:50:58,580 --> 00:51:02,020
And you can close the bookmarks pane,

617
00:51:04,320 --> 00:51:11,140
and do your buyer slicer dropdown
again, and go back to select all.

618
00:51:14,310 --> 00:51:20,480
Our next lesson is about accessibility
features in Power BI reports.

619
00:51:20,481 --> 00:51:23,826
There are two main
categories of features, built-in

620
00:51:23,827 --> 00:51:27,960
accessibility features that
require no configuration,

621
00:51:27,961 --> 00:51:32,180
and built-in accessibility
features requiring configuration.

622
00:51:32,930 --> 00:51:39,280
The features that don't require
configuration are keyboard navigation.

623
00:51:39,281 --> 00:51:45,040
A lot of users want to navigate using
their keyboard through the reports.

624
00:51:45,041 --> 00:51:47,400
There's screen reader compatibility.

625
00:51:48,350 --> 00:51:52,600
If you have high contrast
colors set in Windows,

626
00:51:52,601 --> 00:51:55,620
those high contrast
colors will come over

627
00:51:55,621 --> 00:52:00,620
into Power BI reports and
be applied to your reports.

628
00:52:01,570 --> 00:52:05,120
You have focus mode so
you can fill up the whole canvas

629
00:52:05,270 --> 00:52:09,720
and just focus on the
visualization that you're looking at.

630
00:52:09,721 --> 00:52:15,880
And another one that requires no configuration
is the ability to show a data table

631
00:52:15,881 --> 00:52:20,400
of the underlying data for
that particular visualization.

632
00:52:20,401 --> 00:52:23,980
You'll get to see some of these
as we go through this lesson.

633
00:52:25,230 --> 00:52:30,240
We also have features
that do require configuration.

634
00:52:30,340 --> 00:52:36,800
In this lesson, we'll go through alt
text, which is text that a screen reader

635
00:52:36,801 --> 00:52:43,160
will read out to the user, making
sure that the tab order is appropriate,

636
00:52:43,310 --> 00:52:48,680
especially for those users that want to
navigate a report by using the keyboard.

637
00:52:48,681 --> 00:52:53,520
There are titles and labels that
can be configured as well as markers,

638
00:52:53,521 --> 00:52:57,680
and you'll get to see
some of the report themes.

639
00:53:01,140 --> 00:53:04,960
The first thing we're
gonna do is configure alt text

640
00:53:05,010 --> 00:53:09,800
for our bar chart on the
sales by category page.

641
00:53:09,850 --> 00:53:14,480
So I've just selected the chart,
and I am gonna go to the format well

642
00:53:14,481 --> 00:53:19,080
in the visualizations
pane and expand general.

643
00:53:19,081 --> 00:53:24,920
If you scroll down, you'll see alt text
at the bottom of the general category.

644
00:53:25,820 --> 00:53:30,860
So if you don't put in alt text,
any screen reader will give

645
00:53:30,861 --> 00:53:37,240
a generic description of whatever
object the end user selects.

646
00:53:37,290 --> 00:53:39,840
So let it just give it
a generic description.

647
00:53:39,841 --> 00:53:43,060
You wanna give a more detailed description.

648
00:53:43,110 --> 00:53:47,880
So in that alt text box, you're
gonna say, you're gonna actually type,

649
00:53:47,881 --> 00:53:52,880
this is a bar graph
representing this year's sales.

650
00:53:58,960 --> 00:54:01,040
Broken down by category.

651
00:54:02,940 --> 00:54:08,356
So when the screen reader
responds to this selected

652
00:54:08,357 --> 00:54:12,180
visualization, that
is the text it will read.

653
00:54:13,730 --> 00:54:17,480
Another accessibility feature
that needs to be configured

654
00:54:17,481 --> 00:54:25,360
via a shortcut key combination is the ability
to add a data table to a visualization.

655
00:54:25,361 --> 00:54:30,360
A data table shows the
underlying data in a table format

656
00:54:30,361 --> 00:54:35,480
that's causing the
visualization to be drawn.

657
00:54:35,530 --> 00:54:39,320
So with that same bar chart selected,

658
00:54:39,321 --> 00:54:47,020
the shortcut key combination for
adding a data table is alt shift F11.

659
00:54:54,360 --> 00:54:58,520
And when you do it, you'll notice
on the bottom half of the screen,

660
00:54:58,521 --> 00:55:02,640
it has a table, a data
table showing a listing

661
00:55:02,641 --> 00:55:07,640
of the categories and each
category sales for this year.

662
00:55:07,641 --> 00:55:12,420
That can be useful when
someone needs to review a report.

663
00:55:13,220 --> 00:55:18,080
You'll notice at the top, it
has a back to report button.

664
00:55:18,081 --> 00:55:21,880
And when you click that button,
it just gets rid of the data table

665
00:55:21,881 --> 00:55:24,700
and takes you back to
the regular report page.

666
00:55:26,750 --> 00:55:30,128
Another useful feature
available for every report

667
00:55:30,129 --> 00:55:35,480
visualization is the ability
to go into focus mode.

668
00:55:35,481 --> 00:55:39,360
In the upper right hand
corner of the bar report,

669
00:55:39,361 --> 00:55:43,160
you'll see the middle
button is focus mode.

670
00:55:43,161 --> 00:55:45,160
I'm gonna click on it.

671
00:55:45,161 --> 00:55:51,280
And this is similar to the type of screen
you get when you put in a data table.

672
00:55:51,281 --> 00:55:53,800
It just doesn't have the data table.

673
00:55:53,801 --> 00:55:57,180
It makes sure that
the visualization fills up

674
00:55:57,230 --> 00:56:01,120
the screen so you can
direct your focus to that.

675
00:56:01,121 --> 00:56:05,880
